goals.question: What is the trend of unemployment rate over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of unemployment rate against year
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a general increase or decrease in unemployment rate over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of unemployment rate across different states?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of unemployment rate against state
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify which states have higher or lower unemployment rates.

goals.question: What is the relationship between unemployment rate and education level?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of unemployment rate against education level
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a correlation between education level and unemployment rate.

goals.question: What is the average duration of unemployment?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the most common duration of unemployment.

goals.question: What is the difference in unemployment rate between genders?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of unemployment rate against gender
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is a difference in unemployment rate between genders.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Unemployment_Rate', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the trend of unemployment rate over the years?', wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='Unemployment Rate', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))
    sns.barplot(x='State', y='Unemployment Rate', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate across different states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Education Level'] = pd.Categorical(data['Education Level'], categories=['Less than high school', 'High school', 'Some college or associate degree', 'Bachelor\'s degree or higher'], ordered=True)
    sns.scatterplot(x='Education Level', y='Unemployment Rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between unemployment rate and education level?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['duration'] = data['duration'].astype(float)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='duration', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['duration'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average duration of unemployment?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    data = data.set_index('Year')
    data = data[['Men', 'Women']]
    data = data.stack().reset_index()
    data.columns = ['Year', 'Gender', 'Unemployment Rate']
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Year', y='Unemployment Rate', hue='Gender', data=data, palette='muted')
    plt.title('What is the difference in unemployment rate between genders?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
